{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1553–1","heading":"Report on in-bond cargo","label":"1553–1 Report on in-bond cargo","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/ch4/stIII/ptIV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationAnother section 553A of act , is classified to .June 17, 1930section 1553a of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Report","label":"a Report","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a plan for closing in-bond entries at the port of arrival;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an assessment of the personnel required to ensure 100 percent reconciliation of in-bond entries between the port of arrival and the port of destination or exportation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an assessment of the status of investigations of overdue in-bond shipments and an evaluation of the resources required to ensure adequate investigation of overdue in-bond shipments;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a plan for tracking in-bond cargo within the Automated Commercial Environment (ACE);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an assessment of whether any particular technologies should be required in the transport of in-bond cargo;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fa%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an assessment of whether ports of arrival should require any additional information regarding shipments of in-bond cargo;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fa%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an evaluation of the criteria for targeting and examining in-bond cargo; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fa%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an assessment of the feasibility of reducing the transit time for in-bond shipments, including an assessment of the impact of such a change on domestic and international trade.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Definition","label":"b Definition","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1553–1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs1553%E2%80%931%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In this section, the term “Commissioner” means the Commissioner responsible for the United States Customs and Border Protection in the Department of Homeland Security.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
